The image is a map titled "VATSIM Germany Sektor Reutlingen (EDDS_REU_APP)." It is designed for flight simulation use only and is not to be used for real-world flight. The map outlines the airspace sector for Reutlingen, with various zones marked with their respective altitude limits and identifiers.

Key features include:
- The central area labeled "REU1" with an altitude limit of 145 GND.
- Surrounding areas with different altitude limits, such as "REU2" with 145 to 395 GND.
- Various other zones with specific altitude limits and identifiers, such as "LFST_SIV," "STG1," "DKB2," "EDDMFUE," and others.
- The map includes boundaries and labels for different airspace sectors and their respective altitude limits.

The map is dated 07.01.2022 and is created by VACC Germany.

The image is a map of the VATSIM Germany airspace, specifically focusing on the Stuttgart sector (EDDS_STG_APP). Surrounding sectors include STG2, STG3, STG5, STG6, and others, each with their own altitude limits. The map is dated 07.01.2022 and is provided by VACC Germany. It is intended for flight simulation use only and not for real-world flight navigation.

metadata.abstract: The document 'EBG 8 [REU, STG]' provides detailed information on the sectors REU (Reutlingen) and STG (Stuttgart) within the Langen FIR. It is intended for flight simulator use only and should not be used for real-world flight. The document includes sector maps, frequencies, and callsigns for both sectors. REU sector handles in- and outbounds from/to the south, as well as traffic to and from EDSB and EDTL. The SOP for REU sector is available at the EDDS SOP. STG sector manages in- and outbounds from/to the north and traffic to and from EDTY. Detailed SOP for STG sector is also available at the EDDS SOP. The document highlights the main sector tasks and provides login information, sector indicators, frequencies, and remarks for both sectors.
